'''Harvey Manger-Weil''' is an [[United States|American]] [[Businessperson|businessman]] and [[entrepreneurship|entrepreneur]] from [[New York City]].<ref name="Entrepreneur">{{cite news | last = Daley | first = Jason | title = Well Enough Alone | publisher = Entrepreneur Magazine | date = 31 May 2012 | url = http://entrepreneurindia.in/people/successinc/well-enough-alone/12066/ | accessdate = 21 April 2014 | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140429201112/http://entrepreneurindia.in/people/successinc/well-enough-alone/12066/ | archivedate = 29 April 2014 | df =  }}</ref> He is best known for his [[SAT]] tutoring business, The College Wizard, in which his stated goal is to help prospective [[college]] students earn better SAT scores.<ref name="RoadMapSolopreneur"/> He has appeared in numerous publications, including ''[[Entrepreneur (magazine)|Entrepreneur]]'' magazine<ref name="Entrepreneur"/> and books like ''Small Business Management''<ref name="SmallBusinessManagement">{{cite book | last =Longenecker | first =Justin | authorlink = |author2=J. William Petty |author3=Leslie E. Palich |author4=Frank Hoy  | title =Small Business Management | publisher =Cengage Learning | series = | volume = | edition = 17 | year =2013 | location = | pages = | language = | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=dZ90AgAAQBAJ&pg=PT225&lpg=PT225&dq=Harvey+manger-weil&source=bl&ots=40pDQfbK74&sig=8dL_MuH2I204BMnBJODZ35Wbjv0&hl=en&sa=X&ei=8C9VU761O_DlyAG4kYDoDw&ved=0CEoQ6AEwBTgy#v=onepage&q=Harvey%20manger-weil&f=false | doi = | id = | isbn =978-1133947752 | mr = | zbl = | jfm = }}</ref> and ''Get Rich Click!''<ref name="GetRichClick">{{cite book | last =Ostrofsky | first =Marc | authorlink = | title =Get Rich Click!: The Ultimate Guide to Making Money on the Internet | publisher =Free Press | series = | volume = | edition = | year =2013 | location = | pages = | language = | url =https://books.google.com/books?id=J1nyTNnVSGAC&pg=PT83&lpg=PT83&dq=Harvey+manger-weil&source=bl&ots=4AaXCFpdFT&sig=BRpwJjjVv87Ptjns6rRI1cD7qgk&hl=en&sa=X&ei=Ti9VU9XoII2FyQG104HYDg&ved=0CEcQ6AEwBjgK#v=onepage&q=Harvey%20manger-weil&f=false | doi = | id = | isbn =978-1451668391 | mr = | zbl = | jfm = }}</ref>

==Early life and education==

Manger-Weil attended [[Dartmouth College]] in the 1970s and graduated with a [[Bachelor of Arts|BA]] in [[philosophy]] in 1980.<ref name="TheDartmouth"/> He began tutoring students for the SATs as an undergraduate at Dartmouth.<ref name="NYC Entrepreneur">{{cite news | last = | first = | title =NYC Entrepreneur Named Best SAT Tutor in America | publisher = Red Orbit| date =3 November 2011 | url =http://www.redorbit.com/news/technology/1112414818/nyc_entrepreneur_named_best_sat_tutor_in_america/ | accessdate = 21 April 2014 }}</ref> He later became an alumni interviewer and enrollment director for his alma mater.<ref name="RoadMapSolopreneur"/><ref name="SmallBusinessManagement"/> At one point, Manger-Weil was a [[Street performance|street musician]] in [[New York City]].<ref name="GetRichClick"/>

==The College Wizard==

After having worked closely with the SAT format for 30 years, Manger-Weil founded the College Wizard in 2010.<ref name="RoadMapSolopreneur"/> He tutors clients one-on-one often through [[Skype]] from his home base in New York City.<ref name="RoadMapSolopreneur"/> He claims to have a system of "7 cardinal rules" that can ensure a perfect score of 2400 on the SAT. He also guarantees noticeable increases in test scores among his clients.<ref name="TheDartmouth"/> His course can take as little as five hours,<ref name="NYC Entrepreneur"/> but can go on longer, until the client is satisfied with their SAT scores.<ref name="TheDartmouth"/> Manger-Weil charges a flat fee for his services, and also provides advice and marketing for gaining entry into the best colleges.<ref name="TheDartmouth"/>

==Other entrepreneurial ventures==
Manger-Weil has engaged in several other entrepreneurial ventures and is heavily involved in the "solopreneur" movement.<ref name="RoadMapSolopreneur"/><ref name="GetRichClick"/> In 2003, he started a [[consulting firm]] geared toward helping people start their own businesses.<ref name="GetRichClick"/> He recently teamed up with fellow solopreneur Bruce Judson in a consulting firm called Your Personal Action Plan, aimed at solo businesspeople on the [[internet]].<ref name="RoadMapSolopreneur"/><ref name="SmallBusinessManagement"/>

In the book ''Get Rich Click!'', Marc Ostrofsky details how Manger-Weil helped earn a second home through effective [[advertising]] with [[AdSense|Google Ads]] for his online businesses.<ref name="GetRichClick"/>

